## 🌐 Global Reskilling & Training Opportunities

Whether you're in Tokyo or Toronto, these international programmes offer free or subsidised training to help you pivot careers, upskill, or explore new industries.

### 🏛️ International Organisations & Initiatives

- **[Reskilling Revolution – World Economic Forum](https://initiatives.weforum.org/reskilling-revolution/skills-initiatives)** – A global initiative aiming to reskill 1 billion people by 2030 through partnerships with governments, businesses, and educators.
- **[ITCILO – International Training Centre of the ILO](https://www.itcilo.org/)** – Offers blended and online training in labour rights, occupational safety, gender equality, and sustainable development. Includes free and paid options.
- **[SIDA International Training Programmes](https://www.sida.se/en/for-partners/international-training-programmes)** – Swedish-funded programmes for professionals in low- and middle-income countries, focusing on reform, sustainability, and human rights.

### 🎓 Global Learning Platforms

- **[Coursera](https://www.coursera.org/)** – Offers free auditing of university-level courses and paid certificates from institutions worldwide.
- **[edX](https://www.edx.org/)** – Learn from Harvard, MIT, and other global universities; audit for free or pay for credentials.
- **[LinkedIn Learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/)** – Subscription-based access to thousands of professional courses.
- **[Udemy](https://www.udemy.com/)** – Affordable courses in tech, business, and personal development.
- **[FutureLearn](https://www.futurelearn.com/)** – UK-based platform offering global courses in communication, digital skills, and career development.

### 🌍 Regional & Sponsored Programmes

- **[IATSS Forum Leadership Program – Japan](https://www.opportunitiescircle.com/blog/international-training-programs/)** – Fully funded leadership training for young professionals across Asia.
- **[Swedish Institute SAYP Training Program](https://www.opportunitiescircle.com/blog/international-training-programs/)** – Covers travel, accommodation, and mentorship for participants from non-EU countries.
- **[School for International Training (SIT)](https://www.sit.edu/)** – Offers over 90 degree and training programmes across seven continents.
